         <div type="apparatus">
            <listApp>
               <app loc="1"><note>Traces of three letters seen by Heberdey, none by me</note></app> 
           <app loc="3"><note>ΠΡΑϹΙΝ written in a rasura; the letters below are not apparent. Heberdey Β under Π, Τ under Ν</note></app>
           <app loc="4"><note>Π: Heberdey saw an upright</note></app>
            <app loc="4"><note>Λ is written Α, suggesting that errors are possible in this text</note></app>
            </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve">
           <p>Many years for Christian emperors and Greens!
</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>In line 3 Πραϲίνων, Greens, appears to have been written over Βενέτων, Blues. This might reflect internal tensions, but is perhaps more likely to indicate a simple error. 
               This stone is clearly a partner one now lost in the opposite corner; it is likely that they were intended to name each of the two colours.</p> 
         </div>
         
